Spot Equities positioning / Volâ€¦

This "Fed is cutting into ğŸš€ asset and commodity prices" is very popular and logically make sense as a concern

Historically, Energy has risen ~15% in the 6 months leading into a cutting cycle and broader commodities have risen ~3.4% on average over the same period âœ…

At the inflection of the tightening/restrictive change to easing, precious metals begin to pick up steam while other commodities settle down âœ…

The following 3-6-9 months later, previous metals (+9-12%) and energy (+6%) tend to perform rather well while other commodities have mixed-to-negative trends ğŸš€

Notably, broader commodities tend to respond with about a 3-5 month lag with about +3.5% ğŸš€ for every 100 bps drop in real rates (2y)

The monetary impact buoys gold, etc., while the economic concerns and investment allocation tradeoffs soften cyclical commodities, broader equities, etc.

Moreover, markets tend to front-run obvious policy transitions which is why the performance tends to be better heading INTO the cutting cycle... after all, Fed Funds basically follows the 2y with a 26 week lag.

As always, the go-forward performance is the fight between the denominator (USD) and the numerator (Economy)
